{
  "id": "extended-diagnostics/NG8109",
  "title": "NG8109: Signals must be invoked in template interpolations.",
  "contents": "<div class=\"content\">\n\n  <h1 id=\"ng8109-signals-must-be-invoked-in-template-interpolations\">NG8109: Signals must be invoked in template interpolations.<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"extended-diagnostics/NG8109#ng8109-signals-must-be-invoked-in-template-interpolations\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n\n  <div class=\"diagnostic-description\">\n    <h2 id=\"description\">Description<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"extended-diagnostics/NG8109#description\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n    <p>Angular Signals are zero-argument functions (<code>() => T</code>). When executed, they return the current value of the signal.\nThis means they are meant to be invoked when used in template interpolations to render its value.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-should-i-do-instead\">What should I do instead?<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"extended-diagnostics/NG8109#what-should-i-do-instead\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>When you use a signal within a template interpolation, you need to invoke it to render its value. </p>\n<code-example format=\"typescript\" language=\"typescript\">\n\nimport {<a href=\"api/core/Component\" class=\"code-anchor\">Component</a>, <a href=\"api/core/signal\" class=\"code-anchor\">signal</a>, <a href=\"api/core/Signal\" class=\"code-anchor\">Signal</a>} from '@angular/core';\n\n@<a href=\"api/core/Component\" class=\"code-anchor\">Component</a>({\n  // â€¦\n})\nclass MyComponent {\n    mySignal: <a href=\"api/core/Signal\" class=\"code-anchor\">Signal</a><number> = <a href=\"api/core/signal\" class=\"code-anchor\">signal</a>(0)\n}\n</number></code-example>\n<code-example format=\"html\" language=\"html\">\n &#x3C;div>{{ mySignal() }}/div>\n</code-example>\n<!-- links -->\n<!-- external links -->\n<!-- end links -->\n\n  </div>\n\n</div>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - extended-diagnostics\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - api/core/Component\n - api/core/Signal\n - api/core/signal\n - extended-diagnostics/NG8109#description\n - extended-diagnostics/NG8109#ng8109-signals-must-be-invoked-in-template-interpolations\n - extended-diagnostics/NG8109#what-should-i-do-instead\n-->"
}